version 1.0

import "DeliveryTasks.wdl" as cloudDeliveryTasks
import "MultiSampleArrays.wdl" as multiSampleArrays

# Combine samples output into a VCF and deliver outputs and the VCF
# to a FireCloud workspace.
#
workflow ArraysDataDelivery {

  String pipeline_version = "1.10.0"

  input {
    String? authorization_domain

    String billing_project

    String environment
    String requester
    File chipwellbarcode_version_tsv

    String clio_url

    # Specify this to skip the MultiSampleArrays subworkflow.
    #
    File? multi_sample_vcf
    Boolean clean_up_source_multi_sample = false

    String workspace_name

    File? samples_metadata

    Int preemptible_tries

    File compute_service_account_json
    File service_account_json

    String? sample_set
    String sample_set_name = select_first([sample_set, workspace_name])

    String? description
    String description_name = select_first([description, workspace_name])

    Boolean deliver_metadata
    Boolean deliver_multi_sample_vcf
    Boolean override_delivery_check
    Boolean fee_for_service
    Boolean clinical

    String? methods_dev # For testing purposes

    Array[String]? extra_grant_reader_users

    Int scatter_batch_size = 100
  }

  String library_curator_email = "GROUP_DSP_library_curator@firecloud.org"
  String methods_dev_email = select_first([methods_dev, "GROUP_MethodsDev@firecloud.org"])

  String cromwell_service_account = "cromwell@broad-gotc-prod.iam.gserviceaccount.com"
  String cromwell_developer_account = "879176801476-compute@developer.gserviceaccount.com"
  String bucket_sample_set_destination_prefix = "gs://~{createWorkspace.bucket}/~{sample_set_name}/"

  # Make sure there hasn't been a repatienting.
  call CheckArraysRepatienting {
    input:
      chipwellbarcode_version_tsv = chipwellbarcode_version_tsv,
      environment = environment,
      preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries
  }

  # Fail unless the calling user is in FireCloud's
  # authorization_domain when authorization_domain is defined.
  #
  if (defined(authorization_domain)) {
    call cloudDeliveryTasks.CheckAuthDomainGroup as checkAuthDomainGroup {
      input:
        authorization_domain = select_first([authorization_domain]),
        service_account_json = service_account_json
      }
  }

  # Divide the rows of the input TSV into groups of N.
  # It's more efficient to do some sequential processing for smallish batches
  # within tasks than it is to scatter one-task-per-row.
  #
  call cloudDeliveryTasks.SplitFile as splitInputs {
    input:
      file = chipwellbarcode_version_tsv,
      lines_per_group = scatter_batch_size,
      preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries
    }

  scatter (subset in splitInputs.file_splits) {
    # Filter blacklisted barcodes out of TSV file.
    #
    call CheckArraysBlacklist {
      input:
        environment = environment,
        chipwellbarcode_version_tsv = subset,
        preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries
      }

    # Batch-query Clio for relevant data needed in downstream tasks.
    #
    call GetArrayDataFromClio as getArrayDataFromClio {
      input:
        chipwellbarcode_version_tsv = subset,
        clio_url = clio_url,
        clio_service_account_json = service_account_json,
        preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries
      }

    # Fail when Clio reports that any arrays output is already delivered.
    #
    call CheckIfArraysDelivered as checkIfArraysDelivered {
      input:
        arrays_json = getArrayDataFromClio.arrays,
        workspace_name = workspace_name,
        override_delivery_check = override_delivery_check,
        preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries
      }
  }

  call GetChipReferenceFiles {
    input:
      arrays_jsons = getArrayDataFromClio.arrays,
      preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries
  }

  # Create a FireCloud workspace returning its bucket as output.
  #
  call cloudDeliveryTasks.CreateWorkspace as createWorkspace {
    input:
      workspace_name = workspace_name,
      billing_project = billing_project,
      service_account_json = service_account_json,
      authorization_domain = authorization_domain,
      previous_tasks = [
        length(checkIfArraysDelivered.deliver_arrays) > 0,
        CheckArraysRepatienting.done
      ]
  }

  # Generate a multi-sample VCF for the whole callset if one doesn't already exist.
  #
  if (deliver_multi_sample_vcf && !defined(multi_sample_vcf) &&
      length(checkIfArraysDelivered.deliver_arrays) > 0 &&
      CheckArraysRepatienting.done) {

    call getMultiSampleFiles {
      input:
        arrays_json = getArrayDataFromClio.arrays,
        preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries
      }

    call CheckCanReadForMultiSampleSubworkflow {
      input:
        compute_service_account_json = compute_service_account_json,
        input_lists = [
          getMultiSampleFiles.samples_fofn,
          getMultiSampleFiles.sample_indices_fofn,
          write_lines([
            getMultiSampleFiles.ref_fasta,
            getMultiSampleFiles.ref_fasta_index,
            getMultiSampleFiles.ref_dict
          ])
        ],
        preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries
    }

    call multiSampleArrays.MultiSampleArrays as combineVcfs {
      input:
        samples_fofn = getMultiSampleFiles.samples_fofn,
        sample_indices_fofn = getMultiSampleFiles.sample_indices_fofn,
        ref_fasta = getMultiSampleFiles.ref_fasta,
        ref_fasta_index = getMultiSampleFiles.ref_fasta_index,
        ref_dict = getMultiSampleFiles.ref_dict,
        # Inject an arbitrary dependency on the check for bucket readability...
        callset_name = if CheckCanReadForMultiSampleSubworkflow.can_read then sample_set_name else sample_set_name,
        preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries
      }
  }

  # Deliver arrays outputs for samples in tsvFile to a FireCloud workspace.
  # Needs to run after the multi-sample workflow so we don't move files out
  # from under that wf to an inaccessible bucket.
  #
  scatter (inputs in zip(splitInputs.file_splits, getArrayDataFromClio.arrays)) {
    call DeliverArrays as moveSamples {
      input:
        chipwellbarcode_version_tsv = inputs.left,
        arrays_json = inputs.right,
        clio_url = clio_url,
        clio_service_account_json = service_account_json,
        workspace_name = workspace_name,
        billing_project = billing_project,
        workspace_path = createWorkspace.bucket,
        sample_set_name = sample_set_name,
        force = override_delivery_check,
        multi_sample_vcf = deliverMultiSampleVcf.done
      }
  }

  if (deliver_multi_sample_vcf) {
    # "select_first" a misnomer here: there's no priority order, only one could ever be defined.
    String multi_sample_vcf_to_deliver = select_first([combineVcfs.combined_vcf, multi_sample_vcf])
    String multi_sample_index_to_deliver = select_first([combineVcfs.combined_vcf_index, multi_sample_vcf_to_deliver + ".tbi"])

    String delivered_multi_sample_vcf = bucket_sample_set_destination_prefix + basename(multi_sample_vcf_to_deliver)
    String delivered_multi_sample_index = bucket_sample_set_destination_prefix + basename(multi_sample_index_to_deliver)

    # Move the multi-sample VCF and its index for the whole callset into the workspace bucket.
    # We delay deleting the copied files until the very end of the workflow so we can re-run the
    # task without errors when other parts of the workflow fail.
    #

    call cloudDeliveryTasks.CopyFile as deliverMultiSampleVcf {
      input:
        src = multi_sample_vcf_to_deliver,
        dest = delivered_multi_sample_vcf,
        service_account_json = service_account_json,
        preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries
    }

    # Verify that the associated index file exists in the expected location. If not, generate a
    # new one.
    call VerifyIndexFile as verifyIndexFile {
      input:
        multi_sample_index_location = multi_sample_index_to_deliver,
        multi_sample_vcf_location = multi_sample_vcf_to_deliver,
        service_account_json = service_account_json
    }

    if (verifyIndexFile.index_exists) {
      call cloudDeliveryTasks.CopyFile as deliverExistingMultiSampleVcfIndex {
        input:
          src = multi_sample_index_to_deliver,
          dest = delivered_multi_sample_index,
          service_account_json = service_account_json,
          preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries
      }
    }

    if (!verifyIndexFile.index_exists) {
      call GenerateIndexFile as generateIndexFile {
        input:
          vcf_size = verifyIndexFile.vcf_size,
          multi_sample_vcf_location = multi_sample_vcf_to_deliver,
          preset = "vcf",
          base_name = basename(delivered_multi_sample_vcf),
          service_account_json = service_account_json
      }

      call cloudDeliveryTasks.CopyFile as deliverNewMultiSampleVcfIndex {
        input:
          src = generateIndexFile.index,
          dest = delivered_multi_sample_index,
          service_account_json = service_account_json,
          preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries
      }
    }
  }


  # `addUserReader.done` is hard-coded to return `true`, but Cromwell still has to wait
  # for it to finish running before it knows that. The `if` check therefore delays running
  # `deleteFiles` until after the requester has been added to the workspace & notified.
  #
  if (clean_up_source_multi_sample && deliver_multi_sample_vcf && addUserReader.done &&
      select_first([deliverExistingMultiSampleVcfIndex.done, deliverNewMultiSampleVcfIndex.done])) {
    call cloudDeliveryTasks.DeleteFile as deleteSrcMultiSampleVcf {
      input:
        file_to_delete = select_first([multi_sample_vcf_to_deliver]),
        service_account_json = service_account_json,
        preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries
    }

    if (select_first([verifyIndexFile.index_exists, false])) {
      call cloudDeliveryTasks.DeleteFile as deleteSrcMultiSampleVcfIndex {
        input:
          file_to_delete = select_first([multi_sample_index_to_deliver]),
          service_account_json = service_account_json,
          preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries
      }
    }
  }

  # Copy any extra sample-set-level metadata into the workspace bucket.
  #
  if (defined(samples_metadata)) {
    call cloudDeliveryTasks.CopyFile as copySamplesMetadataFile {
      input:
        src = select_first([samples_metadata]),
        dest = bucket_sample_set_destination_prefix,
        service_account_json = service_account_json,
        preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries
      }
  }

  call cloudDeliveryTasks.CopyFiles as copyCsvAndEgtFiles {
    input:
      sources = [GetChipReferenceFiles.extended_chip_manifest_path,
                 GetChipReferenceFiles.cluster_path,
                 GetChipReferenceFiles.bad_assays_manifest_path,
                 GetChipReferenceFiles.non_extended_chip_manifest_path],
      dest = bucket_sample_set_destination_prefix,
      service_account_json = service_account_json,
      preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries
  }

  # Create data-model TSV files for delivering Arrays outputs to a
  # FireCloud workspace bucket.
  #
  call CreateArraysFireCloudConfigFile as createArraysFireCloudConfigFile {
    input:
      environment = environment,
      chipwellbarcode_version_tsv = chipwellbarcode_version_tsv,
      sample_set_name = sample_set_name,
      bucket = createWorkspace.bucket,
      multi_sample_vcf_cloud_path = deliverMultiSampleVcf.copied_file,
      preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries,
      sample_metadata_cloud_path = copySamplesMetadataFile.copied_file
    }

  # Delivery of Metadata Tables to Workspace Data Tab UI vs. Workspace Bucket
  # only copy data model tsv files (sample, participant, etc) to workspace bucket if deliver_metadata = False
  if (!deliver_metadata) {
    # create variable that contains string paths to each of the tsv files and scatter to copy each tsv to workspace bucket destination
    Array[String] data_model_tsvs = [createArraysFireCloudConfigFile.participant,
                                     createArraysFireCloudConfigFile.sample,
                                     createArraysFireCloudConfigFile.sample_set_entity,
                                     createArraysFireCloudConfigFile.sample_set_membership]
    scatter(load_tsv in data_model_tsvs) {
      call cloudDeliveryTasks.CopyFile as CopyTsv {
        input:
          dest = "gs://" + createWorkspace.bucket + "/" + sample_set_name + "/data_model_tsvs/",
          src = load_tsv,
          service_account_json = service_account_json,
          preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries
      }
    }
  }

  # only upload data model tsv files (sample, participant, etc) to workspace data tab if deliver_metadata = True
  if (deliver_metadata) {
    call cloudDeliveryTasks.UploadTsv as uploadParticipants {
      input:
        workspace_name = createWorkspace.workspace,
        billing_project = billing_project,
        service_account_json = service_account_json,
        tsv = createArraysFireCloudConfigFile.participant,
        entity_type = "participant",
        previous_tasks = []
    }

    call cloudDeliveryTasks.SplitTsv as SplitSamples {
      input:
        tsv_to_split = createArraysFireCloudConfigFile.sample,
        prefix = "samples"
    }

    scatter (splitted_sample_tsv in SplitSamples.splitted_tsvs) {
      call cloudDeliveryTasks.UploadTsv as uploadSamples {
        input:
          workspace_name = createWorkspace.workspace,
          billing_project = billing_project,
          service_account_json = service_account_json,
          tsv = splitted_sample_tsv,
          entity_type = "sample",
          previous_tasks = [uploadParticipants.done]
      }
    }

    call cloudDeliveryTasks.UploadSampleSets as uploadSampleSets {
      input:
        workspace_name = createWorkspace.workspace,
        billing_project = billing_project,
        service_account_json = service_account_json,
        sample_set_membership_tsv = createArraysFireCloudConfigFile.sample_set_membership,
        sample_set_entity_tsv = createArraysFireCloudConfigFile.sample_set_entity,
        scattered_samples_uploaded = uploadSamples.num_entities_uploaded,
        previous_tasks = uploadSamples.done
    }
  }

  call cloudDeliveryTasks.GetNumberOfSamples as getNumberOfSamples {
    input:
      workspace_name = createWorkspace.workspace,
      billing_project = billing_project,
      service_account_json = service_account_json,
      preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries,
      tsvs_are_uploaded = uploadSampleSets.done
    }

  # Create JSON files to create the tags and library attributes for
  # an arrays data delivery workspace in FireCloud.
  #
  call GenerateArraysFireCloudCatalogFiles {
    input:
      environment = environment,
      chipwellbarcode_version_tsv = chipwellbarcode_version_tsv,
      workspace_name = workspace_name,
      requester = requester,
      number_of_total_samples = getNumberOfSamples.number_of_total_samples,
      preemptible_tries = preemptible_tries
    }

  # PATCH the workspaceName with the Arrays tagFile.
  #
  call cloudDeliveryTasks.AddTags as addTags {
    input:
      service_account_json = service_account_json,
      billing_project = billing_project,
      workspace_name = workspace_name,
      tag_file = GenerateArraysFireCloudCatalogFiles.tag_file,
      previous_tasks = [createWorkspace.done]
    }

  # PATCH the description with addDescription.
  #
  call cloudDeliveryTasks.AddDescription as addDescription {
    input:
      workspace_name = workspace_name,
      billing_project = billing_project,
      service_account_json = service_account_json,
      description = description_name,
      previous_tasks = [createWorkspace.done]
    }


  # PATCH workspaceName metadata with libraryAttrsFile.
  #
  call cloudDeliveryTasks.UpdateLibraryMetadata as updateLibraryMetadata {
    input:
      service_account_json = service_account_json,
      billing_project = billing_project,
      workspace_name = workspace_name,
      library_attrs_file = GenerateArraysFireCloudCatalogFiles.library_attributes,
      previous_tasks = [createWorkspace.done]
    }

  # PATCH workspaceName with the service account as CATALOGer.
  #
  call cloudDeliveryTasks.AddCataloger as addServiceAccountAsCataloger {
    input:
      workspace_name = workspace_name,
      billing_project = billing_project,
      service_account_json = service_account_json,
      email = "",
      previous_tasks = [createWorkspace.done]
    }

  # PATCH workspaceName with the requester as CATALOGer.
  #
  call cloudDeliveryTasks.AddCataloger as addUserCataloger  {
    input:
      workspace_name = workspace_name,
      billing_project = billing_project,
      service_account_json = service_account_json,
      email = requester,
      previous_tasks = [createWorkspace.done]
    }

  # PATCH workspaceName with the Arrays libraryAttrsFile.
  #
  call cloudDeliveryTasks.PublishInLibrary as publishInLibrary {
    input:
      service_account_json = service_account_json,
      billing_project = billing_project,
      workspace_name = workspace_name,
      previous_tasks = [addServiceAccountAsCataloger.done,
                    addTags.done,
                    addUserCataloger.done,
                    updateLibraryMetadata.done]
    }

    if (!fee_for_service && !clinical) {

      # Make sure we add the library curator as a READER first
      call cloudDeliveryTasks.AddUser as addCuratorReader  {
        input:
          workspace_name = workspace_name,
          service_account_json = service_account_json,
          billing_project = billing_project,
          email = library_curator_email,
          access_level = "READER",
          can_share = false,
          previous_tasks = [createWorkspace.done]
        }

      # Only after the library curator is added as a READER, add as Cataloger
      call cloudDeliveryTasks.AddCataloger as addCuratorCataloger  {
        input:
          workspace_name = workspace_name,
          service_account_json = service_account_json,
          billing_project = billing_project,
          email = library_curator_email,
          previous_tasks = [
            createWorkspace.done,
            addCuratorReader.done
          ]
        }

      call cloudDeliveryTasks.AddUser as addMethodsDevReader  {
        input:
          workspace_name = workspace_name,
          service_account_json = service_account_json,
          billing_project = billing_project,
          email = methods_dev_email,
          access_level = "READER",
          can_share = false,
          previous_tasks = [createWorkspace.done]
        }
    }

  call cloudDeliveryTasks.AddUser as addCromwellServiceReader {
    input:
      service_account_json = service_account_json,
      billing_project = billing_project,
      workspace_name = workspace_name,
      email = cromwell_service_account,
      access_level = "READER",
      can_share = false,
      previous_tasks = [publishInLibrary.done]
    }

  call cloudDeliveryTasks.AddUser as addCromwellDeveloperReader {
    input:
      service_account_json = service_account_json,
      billing_project = billing_project,
      workspace_name = workspace_name,
      email = cromwell_developer_account,
      access_level = "READER",
      can_share = false,
      previous_tasks = [publishInLibrary.done]
    }

  if (defined(extra_grant_reader_users)) {
    Array[String] defined_extra_grant_reader_users = select_first([extra_grant_reader_users])
    scatter(user in defined_extra_grant_reader_users) {
      call cloudDeliveryTasks.AddUser as addGrantReader {
        input:
          service_account_json = service_account_json,
          billing_project = billing_project,
          workspace_name = workspace_name,
          email = user,
          access_level = "READER",
          can_share = true,
          previous_tasks = [publishInLibrary.done]
      }
    }
  }

  # This has to be the last call because it notifies the requester.
  # PATCH workspaceName with the requester as READER.
  #
  call cloudDeliveryTasks.AddUser as addUserReader {
    input:
      service_account_json = service_account_json,
      billing_project = billing_project,
      workspace_name = workspace_name,
      email = requester,
      access_level = "READER",
      can_share = true,
      previous_tasks = [publishInLibrary.done]
    }

  output {
    String workspace_bucket = createWorkspace.bucket
  }
}


task CheckArraysRepatienting {
  input {
    File chipwellbarcode_version_tsv
    String environment
    Int preemptible_tries
  }

  command <<<
    set -e -o pipefail

    java -Xmx2g -jar /usr/gitc/picard-private.jar \
       ValidateArraysVersionAndSampleAlias \
       DB_JDBC_FILE=/usr/gitc/cloudsql.db_jdbc.txt \
       DB_PASSWORD_FILE=/usr/gitc/cloudsql.db_password.txt \
       DB_USERNAME_FILE=/usr/gitc/cloudsql.db_username.txt \
       ENVIRONMENT='~{environment}' \
       TSV='~{chipwellbarcode_version_tsv}'
  >>>

  runtime {
    preemptible: preemptible_tries
    memory: "3.5 GiB"
  }

  output {
    Boolean done = true
  }
}


task GetArrayDataFromClio {
  input {
    File chipwellbarcode_version_tsv
    String clio_url
    File clio_service_account_json

    String query_in = "query.json"

    String arrays_json = "arrays.json"
    Int preemptible_tries
  }

  command <<<
    set -e -o pipefail

    function oneShould () {
      local -r indent='        ' barcode=$1 version=$2
      local -r -a lines=(
        '{'
        '  "bool": {'
        '    "must": ['
        '      {"term": {"chipwell_barcode": "'"$barcode"'"}},'
        '      {"term": {"version": '"$version"'}}'
        '    ]'
        '  }'
        '}')
      local line
      for line in "${lines[@]}"
      do
        echo "$indent$line"
      done
    }

    function allShoulds () {
      local -r tsv=$1
      local barcode version comma
      while read barcode version || test -n "$barcode$version"
      do
        echo "$comma$(oneShould $barcode $version)"
        comma=,
      done < "$tsv"
    }

    function makeQuery () {
      local -r tsv=$1
      local -r -a lines=(
        '{'
        '  "_source": ['
        '    "chipwell_barcode", "version", "workspace_name", "research_project_id", "sample_alias",'
        '    "vcf_path", "vcf_index_path", "ref_fasta_path", "ref_fasta_index_path", "ref_dict_path",'
        '    "chip_type", "extended_chip_manifest_path", "cluster_path"'
        '  ],'
        '  "query" : {'
        '    "bool": {'
        '      "should": ['
        "$(allShoulds $tsv)"
        '      ],'
        '      "minimum_should_match": 1'
        '    }'
        '  }'
        '}'
      )
      local line
      for line in "${lines[@]}"
      do
        echo "$line"
      done > '~{query_in}'
    }

    function runQuery () {
      java -Dclio.server.hostname='~{clio_url}' \
         -Dclio.server.port=443 \
         -Dclio.server.use-https=true \
         -Dclio.client.service-account-json='~{clio_service_account_json}' \
         -jar /usr/gitc/clio-client.jar \
         raw-query-arrays \
         --query-input-path '~{query_in}' | jq -c . > '~{arrays_json}'
    }

    makeQuery '~{chipwellbarcode_version_tsv}'
    runQuery
  >>>

  runtime {
    preemptible: preemptible_tries
  }

  output {
    File arrays = arrays_json
  }
}


task GetChipReferenceFiles {
  input {
    Array[File] arrays_jsons
    Int preemptible_tries
  }

  command <<<
    set -e -o pipefail
    jq -s add ~{sep=' ' arrays_jsons} > all_arrays.json

    jq -r .[].chip_type all_arrays.json | uniq > chip_types
    jq -r .[].extended_chip_manifest_path all_arrays.json | uniq > extended_chip_manifest_paths
    jq -r .[].cluster_path all_arrays.json | uniq > cluster_paths

    if [ "$(cat chip_types | wc -l)" -ne 1 ]; then
      >&2 echo The chip_types were not all the same
      exit 1
    fi

    if [ "$(cat extended_chip_manifest_paths | wc -l)" -ne 1 ]; then
      >&2 echo The extended_chip_manifest_paths were not all the same
      exit 1
    fi

    if [ "$(cat cluster_paths | wc -l)" -ne 1 ]; then
      >&2 echo The cluster_paths were not all the same
      exit 1
    fi

    CHIP_REFERENCE_DIR=$(dirname $(cat cluster_paths))
    echo $CHIP_REFERENCE_DIR/$(cat chip_types).csv > non_extended_chip_manifest_path
    echo $(cat extended_chip_manifest_paths | sed s/.extended.csv/.bad_assays.csv/) > bad_assays_manifest_path
  >>>

  runtime {
    preemptible: preemptible_tries
  }

  output {
    String extended_chip_manifest_path = read_string("extended_chip_manifest_paths")
    String cluster_path = read_string("cluster_paths")
    String bad_assays_manifest_path = read_string("bad_assays_manifest_path")
    String non_extended_chip_manifest_path = read_string("non_extended_chip_manifest_path")
  }
}


task CheckIfArraysDelivered {
  input {
    File arrays_json
    String workspace_name
    Boolean override_delivery_check
    Int preemptible_tries
  }

  String already_delivered_file = "already-delivered-arrays.json"

  command <<<
    set -e -o pipefail

    jq -c '[ .[] | select(.workspace_name != "~{workspace_name}") | select(.workspace_name != "") | select(.workspace_name != null) ]' \
       '~{arrays_json}' > '~{already_delivered_file}'

    if test "$(jq '.|length' ~{already_delivered_file})" -gt 0
    then
      >&2 echo Some arrays have already been delivered!

task DeliverArrays {
  input {
    File chipwellbarcode_version_tsv
    File arrays_json

    String clio_url
    File clio_service_account_json

    String workspace_name
    String billing_project
    String workspace_path
    String sample_set_name

    Boolean force

    # Not used, just sets up a task dependency:
    Boolean? multi_sample_vcf

    Int parallelism = 4
  }

  command <<<
    set -e -o pipefail

    function deliver_one_array () {
      set -e -o pipefail

      local -r chipwell_barcode="$1"
      local -r version="$2"

      JAVA=(java -Xmx512m
          -Dclio.server.hostname='~{clio_url}'
          -Dclio.server.port=443
          -Dclio.server.use-https=true
          -Dclio.client.service-account-json='~{clio_service_account_json}'
          -jar /usr/gitc/clio-client.jar)

      local -r json="${chipwell_barcode}_${version}.json"

      jq '.[] | select(.chipwell_barcode == "'"$chipwell_barcode"'" and .version == '"$version"')' '~{arrays_json}' > "$json"

      >&2 echo Using data for $chipwell_barcode v$version:
      >&2 jq . "$json"
      >&2 echo

      RESEARCH_PROJECT_ID=$(jq -r .research_project_id "$json")
      SAMPLE_ALIAS=$(jq -r .sample_alias "$json")

      WSNAMES=('~{workspace_path}'
           '~{sample_set_name}'
           "$RESEARCH_PROJECT_ID"
           "$SAMPLE_ALIAS"
           "$chipwell_barcode"
           "v$version")

      # See GCS_UNSAFE_CHARS in CreateArraysFireCloudConfigFile.
      #
      GCS_UNSAFE_CHARS='()#/ \t'
      WSPATH=gs://
      for name in "${WSNAMES[@]}"
      do
        name=$(echo "$name" | tr "$GCS_UNSAFE_CHARS" _)
        WSPATH="$WSPATH$name/"
      done

      DELIVER=("${JAVA[@]}" deliver-arrays
           --location GCP
           --chipwell-barcode "$chipwell_barcode"
           --version "$version"
           ~{true='--force' false='' force}
           --workspace-name '~{workspace_name}'
           --billing-project '~{billing_project}'
           --workspace-path "$WSPATH")

      >&2 echo Running: "${DELIVER[@]}"
      "${DELIVER[@]}"
      >&2 echo Successfully delivered $chipwell_barcode v$version to ${workspace_name}
    }
    export -f deliver_one_array

    # Run deliveries in parallel.
    PARALLEL=(parallel
          # Push the function into the environments of the parallel sub-processes.
          --env deliver_one_array
          # Limit the number of parallel jobs to whatever was given as input.
          # Other jobs will sit and wait until a slot frees up.
          --jobs '~{parallelism}'
          # Parse the arg file as a TSV.
          --colsep '\t'
          # For each row of the arg file, run the function with the 1st column
          # as the 1st arg and the 2nd column as the 2nd arg.
          # parallel might do that by default already, but I like to be explicit.
          'deliver_one_array {1} {2}')

    # Override the default shell so the function still works
    # (parallel picks up the system-default shell, which on alpine is /bin/ash).
    #
    # '::::' means "interpret the next symbol as the name of a file containing arguments
    #         for the jobs to run, with one set of args per line".
    SHELL=$(which bash) "${PARALLEL[@]}" :::: '~{chipwellbarcode_version_tsv}'
  >>>

  runtime {
    cpu: parallelism
    memory: (3.75 * parallelism) + " GiB"
    maxRetries: 3
  }

  output {
    Boolean done = true
  }
}


task getMultiSampleFiles {

    Int preemptible_tries
  }

  command <<<
    set -e -o pipefail

    > vcfs.list
    > vcf_indexes.list
    > fastas.list
    > fasta_indexes.list
    > dicts.list

    while read array_json || test -n "$array_json"
    do

      jq -r '.[].vcf_index_path'       "$array_json" >> vcf_indexes.list

    if [ "$(xargs -n1 basename < fastas.list | uniq | wc -l)" -ne 1 ]; then
      >&2 echo The reference fastas were not all the same
      exit 1
    fi

    if [ "$(cat fasta_indexes.list | xargs -n1 basename | uniq | wc -l)" -ne 1 ]; then
      >&2 echo The reference fasta indices were not all the same
      exit 1
    fi

    if [ "$(cat dicts.list| xargs -n1 basename | uniq | wc -l)" -ne 1 ]; then
      >&2 echo The reference fasta dictionaries were not all the same
      exit 1
    fi

    sort -r fastas.list > fastas.sorted.list

    sort -r dicts.list > dicts.sorted.list
  >>>

  runtime {
    preemptible: preemptible_tries
  }

  output {

set -e -o pipefail

token=$(python2 /usr/gitc/hack-token.py '/cromwell_root/broad-arrays-prod-storage/arrays-delivery/gotc-picard-prod-pem.json')
URL='https://api.firecloud.org/api/workspaces/broad-genomics-data/Epi25_NINDS_Neale_CANCAL_Klein_Epilepsy_GRU_GSA-MD/importEntities'

# Can be taken out when FireCloud handles already existing sample in sample_set_membership correctly

# Get full list of samples in workspace.
#
# NOTE: We hit the 'sample_set' endpoint to do this, instead of the 'sample' endpoint, because we
# just uploaded all the samples above, so the 'sample' endpoint will always give us back the full
# list of samples and we'll think there's nothing to do.
#
# On the other hand, the 'sample_set' endpoint will only return data if we've already run a delivery
# against this workspace, becuase the upload call for that endpoint is buried deep in this block.

# Sleep for a bit to let Terra recover
sleep 30
>&2 echo Getting any previously-uploaded sample sets
curl -L -X GET \
     --header "Authorization: Bearer $token" \
     'https://rawls.dsde-prod.broadinstitute.org/api/workspaces/broad-genomics-data/Epi25_NINDS_Neale_CANCAL_Klein_Epilepsy_GRU_GSA-MD/entities/sample_set' \
     > existing_sample_sets.json

>&2 echo Got JSON for existing sample sets:
>&2 jq . existing_sample_sets.json
>&2 echo

jq -r '.[].attributes.samples.items[].entityName' existing_sample_sets.json > existing_samples

>&2 echo Extracted existing sample names:
>&2 cat existing_samples
>&2 echo

# Get full list of samples in new sample_set_membership.tsv
cut -f 2 '/cromwell_root/broad-gotc-prod-cromwell-execution/ArraysDataDelivery/81348706-c966-49a6-852d-cbf2dbc55be6/call-createArraysFireCloudConfigFile/output/sample_set_membership.tsv' | grep -v sample_id > full_list_of_samples_to_upload

>&2 echo Want workspace to contain samples:
>&2 cat full_list_of_samples_to_upload
>&2 echo

# Find samples that are in sample_set_membership that have not been uploaded yet
if [[ $(wc -l < existing_samples) -eq 0 ]]
then
  cp full_list_of_samples_to_upload samples_not_already_included
else
  # '|| true' to handle the case when we've already delivered everything,
  # so inverted-grep legitimately finds no matches.
  grep -Fxv -f existing_samples full_list_of_samples_to_upload > samples_not_already_included || true
fi

>&2 echo Samples not already uploaded:
>&2 cat samples_not_already_included
>&2 echo

# Get full entry from sample_set_membership that need to be included
cat samples_not_already_included | xargs -i sh -c 'grep {} /cromwell_root/broad-gotc-prod-cromwell-execution/ArraysDataDelivery/81348706-c966-49a6-852d-cbf2dbc55be6/call-createArraysFireCloudConfigFile/output/sample_set_membership.tsv' > sample_to_upload

>&2 echo Got membership rows for samples-to-upload:
>&2 cat sample_to_upload
>&2 echo

# Overwrite membership TSV to only include records not-yet-uploaded.
head -1 '/cromwell_root/broad-gotc-prod-cromwell-execution/ArraysDataDelivery/81348706-c966-49a6-852d-cbf2dbc55be6/call-createArraysFireCloudConfigFile/output/sample_set_membership.tsv' > header
cat sample_to_upload >> header
mv header sample_set_membership_to_upload.tsv

# Check if the membership TSV contains anything but the header.
uploaded_sample_set_memberships=true
if [[ $(wc -l < sample_set_membership_to_upload.tsv) -ge 2 ]]
then
  # Sleep for a bit to let Terra recover
  sleep 30
  >&2 echo "Uploading filtered membership TSV"
  curl -L -X POST \
       --header "Authorization: Bearer $token" \
       -F 'entities=@sample_set_membership_to_upload.tsv' \
       $URL \
       > sample_set_output.txt

  sample_set_response=$(< sample_set_output.txt)
  if [ "$sample_set_response" != sample_set ]; then
    >&2 echo "There was an error uploading the sample-set memberships"
    >&2 echo "$sample_set_response"
    exit 1
  fi
else
  >&2 echo "All samples already registered as members of a sample-set"
  sample_set_response=sample_set
  uploaded_sample_set_memberships=false
fi

# Sleep for a bit to let Terra recover
sleep 30

if [[ $(echo 0 | bc) -eq 0 ]]; then
  uploaded_samples=false
else
  uploaded_samples=true
fi

if $uploaded_samples || $uploaded_sample_set_memberships; then
  >&2 echo "Uploading sample-set entity TSV"
  curl -L -X POST \
       --header "Authorization: Bearer $token" \
       -F 'entities=@/cromwell_root/broad-gotc-prod-cromwell-execution/ArraysDataDelivery/81348706-c966-49a6-852d-cbf2dbc55be6/call-createArraysFireCloudConfigFile/output/sample_set_entity.tsv' \
       $URL \
       > sample_set_entity_output.txt
  sample_set_entity_response=$(< sample_set_entity_output.txt)
  if [ "$sample_set_entity_response" == sample_set ]; then
    >&2 echo "Successfully uploaded sample-set entity TSV"

    >&2 echo "$sample_set_entity_response"
    exit 1
  fi
else
  >&2 echo "No new samples or sample set memberships uploaded. Skipping uploading sample_set_entity"
fi

function oneShould () {
  local -r indent='        ' barcode=$1 version=$2
  local -r -a lines=(
    '{'
    '  "bool": {'
    '    "must": ['
    '      {"term": {"chipwell_barcode": "'"$barcode"'"}},'
    '      {"term": {"version": '"$version"'}}'
    '    ]'
    '  }'
    '}')
  local line
  for line in "${lines[@]}"
  do
    echo "$indent$line"
  done
}

function allShoulds () {
  local -r tsv=$1
  local barcode version comma
  while read barcode version || test -n "$barcode$version"
  do
    echo "$comma$(oneShould $barcode $version)"
    comma=,
  done < "$tsv"
}

function makeQuery () {
  local -r tsv=$1

    "$(allShoulds $tsv)"

    '    }'
    '  }'
    '}'
  )
  local line
  for line in "${lines[@]}"
  do
    echo "$line"
  done > 'query.json'
}

set -e -o pipefail

function deliver_one_array () {
  set -e -o pipefail

  local -r chipwell_barcode="$1"
  local -r version="$2"

  JAVA=(java -Xmx512m
      -Dclio.server.hostname='clio.gotc-prod.broadinstitute.org'
      -Dclio.server.port=443
      -Dclio.server.use-https=true
      -Dclio.client.service-account-json='/cromwell_root/broad-arrays-prod-storage/arrays-delivery/gotc-picard-prod-pem.json'
      -jar /usr/gitc/clio-client.jar)

  local -r json="${chipwell_barcode}_${version}.json"

  jq '.[] | select(.chipwell_barcode == "'"$chipwell_barcode"'" and .version == '"$version"')' '/cromwell_root/broad-gotc-prod-cromwell-execution/ArraysDataDelivery/81348706-c966-49a6-852d-cbf2dbc55be6/call-getArrayDataFromClio/shard-0/arrays.json' > "$json"

  >&2 echo Using data for $chipwell_barcode v$version:
  >&2 jq . "$json"
  >&2 echo

  RESEARCH_PROJECT_ID=$(jq -r .research_project_id "$json")
  SAMPLE_ALIAS=$(jq -r .sample_alias "$json")

  WSNAMES=('fc-81f3db16-852f-4148-89e8-799145102118'
       'Epi25_NINDS_Neale_CANCAL_Klein_Epilepsy_GRU_GSA-MD_Year7'
       "$RESEARCH_PROJECT_ID"
       "$SAMPLE_ALIAS"
       "$chipwell_barcode"
       "v$version")

  # See GCS_UNSAFE_CHARS in CreateArraysFireCloudConfigFile.
  #
  GCS_UNSAFE_CHARS='()#/ \t'
  WSPATH=gs://
  for name in "${WSNAMES[@]}"
  do
    name=$(echo "$name" | tr "$GCS_UNSAFE_CHARS" _)
    WSPATH="$WSPATH$name/"
  done

  DELIVER=("${JAVA[@]}" deliver-arrays
       --location GCP
       --chipwell-barcode "$chipwell_barcode"
       --version "$version"
       
       --workspace-name 'Epi25_NINDS_Neale_CANCAL_Klein_Epilepsy_GRU_GSA-MD'
       --billing-project 'broad-genomics-data'
       --workspace-path "$WSPATH")

  >&2 echo Running: "${DELIVER[@]}"
  "${DELIVER[@]}"
  >&2 echo Successfully delivered $chipwell_barcode v$version to ${workspace_name}
}
export -f deliver_one_array

# Run deliveries in parallel.
PARALLEL=(parallel
      # Push the function into the environments of the parallel sub-processes.
      --env deliver_one_array
      # Limit the number of parallel jobs to whatever was given as input.
      # Other jobs will sit and wait until a slot frees up.
      --jobs '4'
      # Parse the arg file as a TSV.
      --colsep '\t'
      # For each row of the arg file, run the function with the 1st column
      # as the 1st arg and the 2nd column as the 2nd arg.
      # parallel might do that by default already, but I like to be explicit.
      'deliver_one_array {1} {2}')

# Override the default shell so the function still works
# (parallel picks up the system-default shell, which on alpine is /bin/ash).
#
# '::::' means "interpret the next symbol as the name of a file containing arguments
#         for the jobs to run, with one set of args per line".
SHELL=$(which bash) "${PARALLEL[@]}" :::: '/cromwell_root/broad-gotc-prod-cromwell-execution/ArraysDataDelivery/81348706-c966-49a6-852d-cbf2dbc55be6/call-splitInputs/glob-ac3bfb5b546d1bd518ca6892452257fc/xaa'
